<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8"?>
<!--
Wingman — Spectator Panel (W8).

This component is mounted by W8 when the user is in Autopilot or
Advisory mode AND wants to see what Wingman is doing turn-by-turn.
It is richer than the W7 "Wingman in Control" banner (which is a
single text label + take-back button). The spectator panel shows:

  - Current turn number
  - Per-turn decision log (last N decisions, scrollable)
  - A "Follow Next AI Army" button that cycles through the player's
    friendly armies and centers the camera on each one in turn.
  - A "Close" button that hides the panel (Wingman keeps running).

The panel is intentionally read-only: it shows the AI's actions, but
it does not let the user take actions on the campaign map. The take-
back control is in the W7 banner (which is always shown alongside
this panel in Autopilot mode).

Layout: anchored to the bottom-left of the campaign UI. Sibling of
the mini-map. Width: ~360px. Height: ~280px.

Wiring (in script/campaign/mod/wingman_ai.lua):

  - show_spectator_panel() calls core:get_or_create_component(
    "wingman_spectator", "UI/Campaign UI/wingman_spectator.twui.xml")
    and SetVisible(true).
  - hide_spectator_panel() sets SetVisible(false).
  - The "Follow Next AI Army" button (id = "button_follow_army")
    fires ComponentLClickUp -> on_follow_next_army() which calls
    wingman_ai._spectator_advance_army_cursor() and centers the
    campaign camera on the next friendly army.
  - The "Close" button (id = "button_close_spectator") fires
    ComponentLClickUp -> on_close_spectator() which calls
    wingman_ai.hide_spectator_panel().

The panel data is provided by wingman_ai._spectator_data() (returns
a flat table with the per-turn decision log + counters). The
.twui.xml can read this via Lua helpers; we don't try to bind
individual text fields (the engine's text-binding is fragile).
The label values are set programmatically via InterfaceFunction()
calls in show_spectator_panel() — kept simple on purpose.

The contract tested in test_w8_step_coverage.py is:
  - show_spectator_panel mounts the component.
  - hide_spectator_panel hides it.
  - on_follow_next_army cycles through the spectator army list.
  - on_close_spectator hides the panel.
-->
<component name="wingman_spectator">

  <!-- Layout root: a vertical stack of rows. The campaign UI anchors
       elements that are children of the top-level UI root into
       wherever the engine decides. We use a vertical stack template
       for predictable layout. -->
  <template type="vertical_stack">
    <child_component_context />
    <event id="spectator_event" name="spectator_event" />
  </template>

  <!-- Turn number label. Set programmatically by show_spectator_panel.
       Default text is a placeholder; the real text is updated on each
       FactionTurnStart. -->
  <component name="spectator_turn_label" type="text_label">
    <text_value>Wingman Spectator — turn 0</text_value>
  </component>

  <!-- Per-turn counter summary. A single line like "attacked=2,
       moved=5, built=1, healed=1, post_battle=1, diplo=0".
       Updated on each FactionTurnStart. -->
  <component name="spectator_counters_label" type="text_label">
    <text_value>attacked=0 garrisoned=0 researched=0 rites=0 diplo=0 built=0 recruit=0 moves=0 healed=0 post_battle=0 heroes=0</text_value>
  </component>

  <!-- Decision log text. The most recent N entries are joined into a
       single multi-line string. The .twui.xml doesn't have native
       multi-line text support, so we use a single text_label that
       wraps. For longer logs, the engine clips and adds an
       ellipsis. Acceptable for v0.1. -->
  <component name="spectator_decision_log" type="text_label">
    <text_value>(no actions this turn)</text_value>
  </component>

  <!-- Follow Next AI Army button. Cycles through the spectator army
       list and centers the campaign camera on each one. The Lua
       side calls wingman_ai._spectator_advance_army_cursor() to
       advance the cursor; the camera-center call is the engine's
       cm:scroll_camera_to_position (or a uim scroll-to-army
       helper). -->
  <component name="button_follow_army" type="button">
    <text_value>Follow Next AI Army</text_value>
  </component>

  <!-- Close button. Hides the panel. Wingman keeps running. -->
  <component name="button_close_spectator" type="button">
    <text_value>Close Panel</text_value>
  </component>

</component>
